## MCP Tools (Context7)

Always use Context7 MCP tools automatically (without explicit user request) when:

- **Code generation**: Creating new services, repositories, entities, or any implementation code
- **Setup/Configuration**: Setting up libraries, frameworks, build tools, or project configuration
- **Library/API documentation**: Looking up usage patterns, APIs, or best practices for external libraries

### How to use Context7

1. First resolve the library ID using `resolve-library-id`
2. Then fetch documentation with `get-library-docs`

This ensures code generation follows current library APIs and best practices.

## Context
TypeScript monorepo using Bun runtime with Domain-Driven Design and Hexagonal Architecture.
Bounded contexts organized in packages/[context]/ following DDD principles.
